description:
&lt;h2&gt;Are you?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A driven and dynamic Nurse?&lt;br /&gt;An experienced manager within healthcarewanting to take the next step in your career?&lt;br /&gt;Wanting to make a difference to someone’s life?&lt;br /&gt;Ready for a new challenge?&lt;br /&gt;Wanting to work with the best nurses in the UK?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you’ve answered yes to the above then get in touch with our Nurse Recruiter Adam O&#39;Shea on 07834514945&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About The Role :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder is responsible for assuring and improving the quality of care given to patients. Using their own initiative and drawing on Priory and wider healthcare best practice the post-holder will lead on ensuring the hospital has the systems, knowledge and culture in place to deliver, consistently, care that is safe, effective, caring, responsive and well-led. The post-holder has a key role in representing the quality case to stakeholders including the wider Priory Group, CQC and NHSE. In recognition of the importance of the role, the successful applicant will attend and report to Senior Management Team (SMT) meetings .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What you will need :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NMC (Nursing &amp; Midwifery Council registered)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 5 years frontline clinical or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience at ward manager level or equivalent preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And clear experience or knowledge of the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical Governance inspection planning and procedures, audit and reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient sharing of clinical best practice from national bodies such as National Institute for Clinical Excellence (NICE)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to harness the commitment and potential of others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organisational capability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Forward thinking and able to challenge the status quo&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A role model &amp; mentor to other staff - providing advice and support to promote good practice in supervision and reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we’d like to offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Many benefits in line with the NHS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with a dedicated multidisciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free on-site parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhanced maternity pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible benefits including reduced rates and access to new schemes including gym membership, IT technology (laptops / tablets / smartphones) and private healthcare&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to development opportunities including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sponsorship of professional qualifications through our Individual Professional Development (IPD) panel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Long service award&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Subsidised meals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25 days annual leave plus bank holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Birthday Holiday - Your Birthday as an extra days annual leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refer a friend to nursing bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relocation support (including payment for accommodation or moving costs) up to £4000 (Terms apply)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Payment into the pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About Priory Hospital Bristol:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Priory Hospital Bristol is part of the Healthcare Division of Priory Group and has 86 beds over eight wards varying from Eating Disorders, Acute Mental Health, Acquired Brain Injury, CAMHs Tier 4, Huntingdon’s and Dementia.&lt;/p&gt;
